summary: Tony’s Daughter Imagine: The Team Meets Tony’s Baby Mama
title: Tony’s Daughter Imagine: The Team Meets Tony’s Baby Mama
body:
“It’s nice to finally you. By your radiant smile and bright eyes, I can tell your daughter’s looks didn’t come from Tony.”

“Thank you, Thor.”

“So you’re not upset that your boyfriend’s gorgeous, successful baby mama is here?”

“Sam, I’m not jealous. That’s his daughter’s mother.”

“ … anyways, Tony starting singing Don’t You Want Me, Baby to me while I was serving drinks. He kept following me and singing until he fell on a table full of leftover food.”

“Really, Tony? You never serenaded me before.”

“I was drunk … and it’s a catchy song. I do a lot of stupid things when I’m drunk.”

“Tony, how about that KISS concert in ‘94? You starting stripping and you threw your—”

“Okay, okay! That was in the past.”

summary: New headcannon that Tony Stark is the single largest benefactor of the Icelandic Penis Museum, having single-handedly kept it in...
body: New headcannon that Tony Stark is the single largest benefactor of the Icelandic Penis Museum, having single-handedly kept it in operation the past ten years. They wanted to honor him with a portrait, but Pepper managed to convince them not to display it anywhere…prominent. Now every time a janitor opens the broom closet, they’re greeted by a three-foot oil on canvas portrait of Tony Stark himself. Stephen laughed his ass off when he finally saw it.

summary: Tony Stark is the best character bc he’s human, he makes mistakes, we all do, and yes, some of his mistakes were pretty fucking...
body:
Tony Stark is the best character bc he’s human, he makes mistakes, we all do, and yes, some of his mistakes were pretty fucking bad. But at the end of the day, he’s still a “hero.” And that is just so inspirational to me bc you he isn’t some perfect ideal, he’s like you and me. Which is why I don’t understand how so many people can hate on him??? Bc to me he’s a reflection of myself???

Idk, maybe some people watch movies to get away from the flaws and short comings of people, but imo those characters who mess up but fix it are the best.
